	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 13th 10:55 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a level 14 druid (just got SoW, YAY!) and I was trying to solo in Crushbone with some success. I read a few suggestions on various websites regarding various strategies for soloing and, while they seemed to work, I was going crazy trying to keep all my buffs on, keeping my mana up and managing an aggro'd Lego trying to kite it with often resisted Grasping Roots and often fizzled Stinging Swarm.  <br><br>I am not a twink, so my skills are not lacking, but then again, they are not maxxed out for my level due to my varios earlier tactics/spell selections.<br><br>I would like to hear suggestions on the MOST EFFICIENT/SAFEST way to solo in semi-cluttered areas for a druid of my level.  As I stated, I was doing ok, but it didn't take much more than a fizzled GR spell coupled with an add to send me on a corpse run grumbling to myself.<br><br>BTW, I'd appreciate it if the suggestions did not assume 75% or better mana available. What with buff maintenance and all, that is rarely a luxury I can enjoy.<br><br>Rumbledor - Cleric of 12 seasons<br>Othos     - Druid of 14 seasons<br>Brellis   - Wizard of 18 seasons<br>Carne     - Warrior of 14 seasons<br>All in the world of Saryrn.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Rumbledor - Cleric 12<br>Othos - Druid 14<br>Brellis - Wizard 18<br>Carne - Warrior 14<br>All on Saryrn</td></tr>
