<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100870080833358></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100870080833358><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100870080833358>RE: Druid soloing</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100870080833358#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=63996><span id=Scholar>chking</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>23 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 18th 1:40 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.06]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I, too, just reached 14th level, and I have found the Happy Hunting Grounds for druids of our level. Pack for your trip with:<br><br>* Levitate (and bat wings)<br>* Endure Fire<br>* Expulse Summoned<br><br>Now, take a port, punt, or SoW voyage to Lavastorm. Find Lava Crawlers that are yellow to you, and Expulse away! You can kite like mad, and Levitate helps prevent swimming in the lava pools. Expulse has a MUCH better mana/damage ratio (87 damage/60 mana) than Ignite or Stinging Swarm, and the fire beasties don't much care if you Ignite them, so stick to Expulse. Keep Endure Fire up, since Lava Crawlers breathe fire. You can also Expulse elementals and fire imps, but watch the aggro. I have only been here about two hours of game time, and I've earned 3 yellows. Yum! Good luck!<br><br>Lambeau &amp;lt;Lords and Ladies&amp;gt;<br>Druid of Tunare in his 14th season<br>Saryrn server<br>QOTD: &quot;How the heck does a wisp's skin ignite?&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
