<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=1008601303151></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f1008601303151><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=1008601303151>RE: Druid soloing</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=1008601303151#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=128187><span id= >The One and Only madtempest</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 17th 10:01 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a level 30 Druid and solo kiting in LOIO is unbelievably easy to do, especially if there is an enchanter in the zone to give you clarity.<br><br>Root, Immolate (DoT), Creeping Crud (DoT), Combust (180 point DD), Combust (180 point DD = dead grimalkin, sarnak, iksar, etc.<br><br>Any animals in zone is even easier... snare, terrorize animal, then either dot, dot, dd, and finish him off melee, or just snare, terrorize, and melee to save mana.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
